title: Building Geth 1.4.19 with Chocolatey - Godep error
body:
IBM Thinkcentre tower with 2.8GHz processor and 8GB RAM

Geth version: 1.4.19
OS & Version: Windows 7 Pro
Commit hash : (if `develop`)

#### Expected behaviour - Chocolatey should have grabbed dependencies and compiled with last command in Windows wiki


#### Error is generated before compile : No Godeps found.  Geth 1.4.19 compile failure.


#### Ran through all steps in the 1.4 Geth series wiki again and received identical error


![__godep error](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/18013756/20468595/1947ff92-af66-11e6-8838-49a43941dff7.PNG)

Please switch to the `release/1.4` branch before compiling.

    git checkout release/1.4
thanks, will try that
do I do that from the src geth directory or from my command user?
Please run that in `C:\Users\Wagner\src\github.com\ethereum\go-ethereum`.
okey dokels
what next, it has been pointed to geth 1.4, do another go get github.com/tools/godep?
or try godep go install again?

It should work without another `go get` because you already have godep. Maybe try 

    godep go install -v ./...
OK, it is compiling
Might want to add that missing step to the wiki

![___godeps disabled](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/18013756/20468725/8dcb65ec-af67-11e6-94f5-c34f8d09ab1f.PNG)


Godeps says it is disabled, did Geth 1.4.19 compile?  And if so where can I find it?
You can ignore the warning. The real error is that gcc is missing.
Did you install mingw?
Yes I did, did all three choco installs.
Geth is extracting Geth 1.4.19 stuff right now
Sorry, then I'm not sure what the problem is. `choco install mingw` puts gcc into PATH for me.
I'll upload geth 1.4.19 binaries in a few hours.
Opened a command window in win-builds and is extracting stuff.  I ahd winbuilds open

It said it had trouble downloading an external package after mingw install, failed 1, downloaded 0/1, GCC may have been in that download.  Appreciate your help and look forward to builds of 1.4.19.  Not quite ready to make jump to 1.5 Geth series.  Plus 419 is my area code, :smile:
Maybe having win-builds open tied up the GCC package, going to close it and try again
Nope, will just wait for the build.  Thanks.  At least I got to resharpen some of my DOS command line skills.

Was able to get choco install to download mingw package that failed after doing a manual install of MinGW on my tower.  I modified the wiki instructions you gave me to include the 1.4 release install command and everything went fine until it came time to compile build.  see 1st picture for commands I used.  I did not do the mkdir command since it already existed.
![____missing geth pkgs build](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/18013756/20501396/bc6edab4-b007-11e6-9903-10483b896fc0.PNG)

These next 3 pictures show the rest of the pkgs godep go install -v ./... was unable to find in geth directory.
![___missing geth pkgs build 2](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/18013756/20501430/eae3d840-b007-11e6-8c50-71cebf359717.PNG)
![___missinjg geth pkga build 3](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/18013756/20501438/f092aa0a-b007-11e6-9907-84d1add3549a.PNG)
![___missing geth pkgs build 4](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/18013756/20501447/f6af4b46-b007-11e6-9221-5ed8063d1d92.PNG)
grabbed the Geth 1.4.19 source file from go-ethereum release page, I substituted it for the one that Chocolatey fetched and now the build is going through without missing packages.

You can see in this picture the build is compiling without error so far.  It looks like I have my Geth 1.4.19 build.
![____geth godep build success](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/18013756/20501921/da45d5ae-b009-11e6-928f-a16bfa28dc71.PNG)
Great. Please open another issue if there are any further problems.
